Name: The Hustler

Name: Infernal Affairs

Name: Winter Sleep

Name: Brief Encounter
Storyline: Meeting a stranger in a railway station, a woman is tempted to cheat on her husband.

Name: The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari

Name: Fail Safe
Storyline: A technical malfunction sends American planes to Moscow to deliver a nuclear attack. Can all-out war be averted?

Name: Touching the Void

Name: Love Exposure
Storyline: A bizarre love triangle forms between a young Catholic upskirt photographer, a misandric girl and a manipulative cultist.

Name: Persepolis

Name: Crumb
Storyline: An intimate portrait of controversial cartoonist Robert Crumb and his traumatized family.

Name: Manon of the Spring

Name: Day for Night
Storyline: A committed film director struggles to complete his movie while coping with a myriad of crises, personal and professional, among the cast and crew.

Name: Sybil

Name: La strada

Name: Limelight

Name: A Raisin in the Sun

Name: Wit

Name: The Bridge

Storyline: The story focuses on the Holy Grail War and explores the relationship between Shirou Emiya and Sakura Matou, two teenagers participating in this conflict. The story continues immediately ...                See full summary »

Storyline: A documentary showing the life of Bruce Lee up-close.

Storyline: After a bombing raid destroys the family store and her husband, Reiko rebuilds and runs the shop out of love stopped short by destruction.

Storyline: An unlikely connection sparks between two creatures: a fiercely independent stray kitten and a pit bull.

Storyline: In the dead of a Wyoming winter, a bounty hunter and his prisoner find shelter in a cabin currently inhabited by a collection of nefarious characters.

Name: Mississippi Burning
Storyline: Two F.B.I. Agents with wildly different styles arrive in Mississippi to investigate the disappearance of some civil rights activists.

Name: Ghostbusters
Storyline: Three parapsychologists forced out of their university funding set up shop as a unique ghost removal service in New York City, attracting frightened yet skeptical customers.

Name: The Breakfast Club
Storyline: Five high school students meet in Saturday detention and discover how they have a great deal more in common than they thought.

Name: The Big Short
Storyline: In 2006-2007 a group of investors bet against the United States mortgage market. In their research, they discover how flawed and corrupt the market is.

Name: Ferris Bueller's Day Off
Storyline: A popular high school student, admired by his peers, decides to take a day off from school and goes to extreme lengths to pull it off, to the chagrin of his Dean, who'll do anything to stop him.

Name: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
Storyline: Journalist Mikael Blomkvist is aided in his search for a woman who has been missing for 40 years by young computer hacker Lisbeth Salander.

Name: A Bronx Tale
Storyline: Robert De Niro and Chazz Palminteri give captivating performances in this intense drama about a boy torn between his tough, hard-working father and a violent yet charismatic crime boss.

Name: Nightcrawler
Storyline: When Louis Bloom, a con man desperate for work, muscles into the world of L.A. crime journalism, he blurs the line between observer and participant to become the star of his own story.

Name: The Social Network
Storyline: As Harvard student Mark Zuckerberg creates the social networking site that would become known as Facebook, he is sued by the twins who claimed he stole their idea and by the co-founder who was later squeezed out of the business.

Name: Little Miss Sunshine
Storyline: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

Name: Boyz n the Hood
Storyline: Follows the lives of three young males living in the Crenshaw ghetto of Los Angeles, dissecting questions of race, relationships, violence, and future prospects.

Name: Predator
Storyline: A team of commandos on a mission in a Central American jungle find themselves hunted by an extraterrestrial warrior.

Name: Mary Poppins
Storyline: In turn of the century London, a magical nanny employs music and adventure to help two neglected children become closer to their father.

Name: The Fugitive
Storyline: Dr. Richard Kimble, unjustly accused of murdering his wife, must find the real killer while being the target of a nationwide manhunt led by a seasoned U.S. Marshal.

Name: Hot Fuzz
Storyline: A skilled London police officer, after irritating superiors with his embarrassing effectiveness, is transferred to a village where the easygoing officers object to his fervor for regulations, as a string of grisly murders strikes the town.

Name: Manchester by the Sea
Storyline: A depressed uncle is asked to take care of his teenage nephew after the boy's father dies.

Name: Skyfall
Storyline: James Bond's loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. When MI6 comes under attack, 007 must track down and destroy the threat, no matter how personal the cost.

Name: Charade
Storyline: Romance and suspense ensue in Paris as a woman is pursued by several men who want a fortune her murdered husband had stolen. Whom can she trust?

Name: The Untouchables
Storyline: During Prohibition, Treasury agent Eliot Ness sets out to stop ruthless Chicago gangster Al Capone, and assembles a small, incorruptible team to help him.

Name: The Bourne Identity
Storyline: A man is picked up by a fishing boat, bullet-riddled and suffering from amnesia, before racing to elude assassins and attempting to regain his memory.

Name: Serenity
Storyline: The crew of the ship Serenity try to evade an assassin sent to recapture telepath River.

Name: The Fighter
Storyline: Based on the story of Micky Ward, a fledgling boxer who tries to escape the shadow of his more famous but troubled older boxing brother and get his own shot at greatness.

Name: The Sandlot
Storyline: In the summer of 1962, a new kid in town is taken under the wing of a young baseball prodigy and his rowdy team, resulting in many adventures.

Name: Back to the Future Part II
Storyline: After visiting 2015, Marty McFly must repeat his visit to 1955 to prevent disastrous changes to 1985...without interfering with his first trip.

Name: Captain Phillips
Storyline: The true story of Captain Richard Phillips and the 2009 hijacking by Somali pirates of the U.S.-flagged MV Maersk Alabama, the first American cargo ship to be hijacked in two hundred years.

Name: Straight Outta Compton
Storyline: The rap group NWA emerges from the mean streets of Compton in Los Angeles, California, in the mid-1980s and revolutionizes Hip Hop culture with their music and tales about life in the hood.

Name: Moon
Storyline: Astronaut Sam Bell has a quintessentially personal encounter toward the end of his three-year stint on the Moon, where he, working alongside his computer, GERTY, sends back to Earth parcels of a resource that has helped diminish our planet's power problems.

Name: Misery
Storyline: After a famous author is rescued from a car crash by a fan of his novels, he comes to realize that the care he is receiving is only the beginning of a nightmare of captivity and abuse.

Name: I Saw the Devil
Storyline: A secret agent exacts revenge on a serial killer through a series of captures and releases.

Name: Paddington 2
Storyline: Paddington, now happily settled with the Brown family and a popular member of the local community, picks up a series of odd jobs to buy the perfect present for his Aunt Lucy's 100th birthday, only for the gift to be stolen.

Name: Midnight Cowboy
Storyline: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

Name: The Best Offer
Storyline: A lonely art expert working for a mysterious and reclusive heiress finds not only her art worth examining.

Name: The Holy Mountain
Storyline: In a corrupt, greed-fueled world, a powerful alchemist leads a messianic character and seven materialistic figures to the Holy Mountain, where they hope to achieve enlightenment.

Name: Walk the Line
Storyline: A chronicle of country music legend Johnny Cash's life, from his early days on an Arkansas cotton farm to his rise to fame with Sun Records in Memphis, where he recorded alongside Elvis Presley, Jerry Lee Lewis, and Carl Perkins.

Name: Kiki's Delivery Service
Storyline: A young witch, on her mandatory year of independent life, finds fitting into a new community difficult while she supports herself by running an air courier service.

Name: Moonrise Kingdom
Storyline: Two 12-year-olds, who live on an island, fall in love with each other and elope into the wilderness. While people set out on a search mission, a violent storm approaching them catches their attention.

Name: The Devils
Storyline: In 17th-century France, Father Urbain Grandier's protection of the city of Loudun from the corrupt Cardinal Richelieu is undermined by a sexually repressed nun's accusation of witchcraft.

Name: Awakenings
Storyline: The victims of an encephalitis epidemic many years ago have been catatonic ever since, but now a new drug offers the prospect of reviving them.

Name: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
Storyline: A journalist is aided by a young female hacker in his search for the killer of a woman who has been dead for forty years.

Name: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
Storyline: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

Name: The Right Stuff
Storyline: The U.S. space program's development from the breaking of the sound barrier to selection of the Mercury 7 astronauts, from a group of test pilots with a more seat-of-the-pants approach than the program's more cautious engineers preferred.

Name: Let the Right One In
Storyline: Oskar, an overlooked and bullied boy, finds love and revenge through Eli, a beautiful but peculiar girl.

Name: The Remains of the Day
Storyline: A butler who sacrificed body and soul to service in the years leading up to World War II realizes too late how misguided his loyalty was to his lordly employer.

Name: The King of Comedy
Storyline: A passionate yet unsuccessful comedian stalks and kidnaps his idol to take the spotlight for himself.

Name: Isle of Dogs
Storyline: Set in Japan, Isle of Dogs follows a boy's odyssey in search of his lost dog.

Name: The Fall
Storyline: In 1920s Los Angeles, a bedridden patient in a hospital captivates a young girl with a fantastic tale of heroes, myths, and villains on a desert island.

Name: The Outlaw Josey Wales
Storyline: Missouri farmer Josey Wales joins a Confederate guerrilla unit and winds up on the run from the Union soldiers who murdered his family.

Name: The Searchers
Storyline: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a years-long journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches after the rest of his brother's family is massacred in a raid on their Texas farm.

Name: Glory
Storyline: Robert Gould Shaw leads the U.S. Civil War's first all-black volunteer company, fighting prejudices from both his own Union Army, and the Confederates.

Name: The Insider
Storyline: A research chemist comes under personal and professional attack when he decides to appear in a 60 Minutes exposé on Big Tobacco.

Name: Dawn of the Dead
Storyline: During an escalating zombie epidemic, two Philadelphia SWAT team members, a traffic reporter and his TV executive girlfriend seek refuge in a secluded shopping mall.

Name: The World's Fastest Indian
Storyline: The story of New Zealander Burt Munro, who spent years rebuilding a 1920 Indian motorcycle, which helped him set the land speed world record at Utah's Bonneville Salt Flats in 1967.

Name: Changeling
Storyline: Grief-stricken mother Christine Collins takes on the L.A.P.D. to her own detriment when they try to pass off an obvious impostor as her missing child.

Name: Breaking the Waves
Storyline: Oilman Jan is paralyzed in an accident. His wife, who prayed for his return, feels guilty; even more, when Jan urges her to have sex with another.

Name: The Day of the Jackal
Storyline: In the aftermath of France allowing Algeria's independence, a group of resentful military veterans hire a professional assassin codenamed "Jackal" to kill President Charles de Gaulle.

Name: Whisper of the Heart
Storyline: A love story between a girl who loves reading books, and a boy who has previously checked out all of the library books she chooses.

Name: Ed Wood
Storyline: Ambitious but troubled movie director Edward D. Wood Jr. tries his best to fulfill his dreams despite his lack of talent.

Name: My Left Foot
Storyline: Christy Brown, born with cerebral palsy, learns to paint and write with his only controllable limb - his left foot.

Name: Kramer vs. Kramer
Storyline: After his wife leaves him, a work-obsessed Manhattan advertising executive is forced to learn long-neglected parenting skills, but a heated custody battle over the couple's young son deepens the wounds left by the separation.

Name: Pride
Storyline: U.K. gay activists work to help miners during their lengthy strike of the National Union of Mineworkers in the summer of 1984.

Name: Days of Heaven
Storyline: A hot-tempered farm laborer convinces the woman he loves to marry their rich but dying boss so that they can have a claim to his fortune.

Name: Night of the Living Dead
Storyline: A ragtag group of Pennsylvanians barricade themselves in an old farmhouse to remain safe from a horde of flesh-eating ghouls that are ravaging the Northeast of the United States.

Name: Cabaret
Storyline: A female girlie club entertainer in Weimar Republic era Berlin romances two men while the Nazi Party rises to power around them.

Name: The Killing Fields
Storyline: A journalist is trapped in Cambodia during tyrant Pol Pot's bloody 'Year Zero' cleansing campaign, which claimed the lives of two million 'undesirable' civilians.

Name: Aguirre, the Wrath of God
Storyline: In the 16th century, the ruthless and insane Don Lope de Aguirre leads a Spanish expedition in search of El Dorado.

Name: Letters from Iwo Jima
Storyline: The story of the battle of Iwo Jima between the United States and Imperial Japan during World War II, as told from the perspective of the Japanese who fought it.

Name: Freaks
Storyline: A circus' beautiful trapeze artist agrees to marry the leader of side-show performers, but his deformed friends discover she is only marrying him for his inheritance.

Name: Manhattan
Storyline: The life of a divorced television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.

Name: All That Jazz
Storyline: Director/choreographer Bob Fosse tells his own life story as he details the sordid career of Joe Gideon, a womanizing, drug-using dancer.

Name: Once
Storyline: A modern-day musical about a busker and an immigrant and their eventful week in Dublin, as they write, rehearse and record songs that tell their love story.

Name: Frankenstein
Storyline: Dr Henry Frankenstein is obsessed with assembling a living being from parts of several exhumed corpses.

Name: Loving Vincent
Storyline: In a story depicted in oil painted animation, a young man comes to the last hometown of painter Vincent van Gogh to deliver the troubled artist's final letter and ends up investigating his final days there.

Name: Hannah and Her Sisters
Storyline: Between two Thanksgivings two years apart, Hannah's husband falls in love with her sister Lee, while her hypochondriac ex-husband rekindles his relationship with her sister Holly.

Name: The Chaser
Storyline: A disgraced ex-policeman who runs a small ring of prostitutes finds himself in a race against time when one of his women goes missing.

Name: His Girl Friday
Storyline: A newspaper editor uses every trick in the book to keep his ace reporter ex-wife from remarrying.

Name: Lilya 4-Ever
Storyline: Sixteen-year-old Lilja and her only friend, the young boy Volodja, live in Russia, fantasizing about a better life. One day, Lilja falls in love with Andrej, who is going to Sweden, and invites Lilja to come along and start a new life.

Name: Next Goal Wins
Storyline: The American Samoa soccer team, deemed "worst in the world", try to qualify for the 2014 World Cup.

Name: East of Eden
Storyline: Two brothers in 1910s California struggle to maintain their strict, Bible-toting father's favor as an old secret about their long-absent mother comes to light.

Name: Stagecoach
Storyline: A group of people traveling on a stagecoach find their journey complicated by the threat of Geronimo and learn something about each other in the process.

Name: Gaslight
Storyline: Ten years after her aunt was murdered in their London home, a woman returns from Italy in the 1880s to resume residence with her new husband. His obsessive interest in the home rises from a secret that may require driving his wife insane.

Name: Grizzly Man
Storyline: A devastating and heart-rending take on grizzly bear activists Timothy Treadwell and Amie Huguenard, who were killed in October of 2003 while living among grizzly bears in Alaska.

Name: The White Ribbon
Storyline: Strange events happen in a small village in the north of Germany during the years before World War I, which seem to be ritual punishment. Who is responsible?

Name: The Umbrellas of Cherbourg
Storyline: A young woman separated from her lover by war faces a life-altering decision.

Name: Ninja Scroll
Storyline: A vagabond swordsman is aided by a kunoichi and a spy in battling a demonic clan of killers - led by a ghost from his past - who are bent on overthrowing the Tokugawa Shogunate.

Name: Bringing Up Baby
Storyline: While trying to secure a $1 million donation for his museum, a befuddled paleontologist is pursued by a flighty and often irritating heiress and her pet leopard, Baby.

Name: Cowboy Bebop: The Movie
Storyline: A terrorist explosion releases a deadly virus on the masses, and it's up to the bounty-hunting Bebop crew to catch the cold-blooded culprit.

Name: A Prophet
Storyline: A young Algerian man is sent to a French prison.

Name: 12 Angry Men
Storyline: Twelve men must decide the fate of one when one juror objects to the jury's decision.

Name: All About My Mother
Storyline: A comedy-drama about a bereaved mother, and overwrought actress, her jealous lover, and a pregnant nun.

Name: Imitation of Life
Storyline: An aspiring white actress takes in an African American widow whose mixed-race daughter is desperate to be seen as white.

Name: Batman: Mask of the Phantasm
Storyline: Batman is wrongly implicated in a series of murders of mob bosses actually committed by a new vigilante assassin.

Name: Shadow of a Doubt
Storyline: A teenage girl, overjoyed when her favorite uncle comes to visit the family in their quiet California town, slowly begins to suspect that he is in fact the "Merry Widow" killer sought by the authorities.

Name: Land of Mine
Storyline: In post-World War II Denmark, a group of young German POWs are forced to clear a beach of thousands of land mines under the watch of a Danish Sergeant who slowly learns to appreciate their plight.

Name: The Court Jester
Storyline: A hapless carnival performer masquerades as the court jester as part of a plot against an evil ruler who has overthrown the rightful King.

Name: You Can't Take It with You
Storyline: The son of a snobbish Wall Street banker becomes engaged to a woman from a good-natured but decidedly eccentric family not realizing that his father is trying to force her family from their home for a real estate development.

Name: The Man Who Would Be King
Storyline: Two former British soldiers in 1880s India decide to set themselves up as Kings in Kafiristan, a land where no white man has set foot since Alexander the Great.

Name: Johnny Got His Gun
Storyline: During World War I, a patriotic young American is rendered blind, deaf, limbless, and mute by a horrific artillery shell attack. Trapped in what's left of his body, he desperately looks for a way to end his life.

Name: I, Daniel Blake
Storyline: After surviving a heart-attack, a 59-year-old carpenter must fight bureaucratic forces to receive Employment and Support Allowance.

Name: Bride of Frankenstein
Storyline: Mary Shelley reveals the main characters of her novel survived: Dr. Frankenstein, goaded by an even madder scientist, builds his monster a mate.

Name: Red River
Storyline: Dunson leads a cattle drive, the culmination of over 14 years of work, to its destination in Missouri. But his tyrannical behavior along the way causes a mutiny, led by his adopted son.

Name: Amarcord
Storyline: A series of comedic and nostalgic vignettes set in a 1930s Italian coastal town.

Name: To Have and Have Not
Storyline: During World War II, American expatriate Harry Morgan helps transport a French Resistance leader and his beautiful wife to Martinique while romancing a sensuous lounge singer.

Name: Once Upon a Time in Anatolia
Storyline: A group of men set out in search of a dead body in the Anatolian steppes.

Name: The Discreet Charm of the Bourgeoisie
Storyline: A surreal, virtually plotless series of dreams centered around six middle-class people and their consistently interrupted attempts to have a meal together.

Name: The Innocents
Storyline: A young governess for two children becomes convinced that the house and grounds are haunted.

Name: Babette's Feast
Storyline: During the late 19th century, a strict religious community in a Danish village takes in a French refugee from the Franco-Prussian War as a servant to the late pastor's daughters.

Name: Great Expectations
Storyline: A humble orphan boy in 1810s Kent is given the opportunity to go to London and become a gentleman, with the help of an unknown benefactor.

Name: Hud
Storyline: Honest and hard-working Texas rancher Homer Bannon has a conflict with his unscrupulous, selfish, arrogant and egotistical son Hud, who sank into alcoholism after accidentally killing his brother in a car crash.

Name: Like Father, Like Son
Storyline: Ryota is a successful workaholic businessman. When he learns that his biological son was switched with another boy after birth, he faces the difficult decision to choose his true son or the boy he and his wife have raised as their own.

Name: The Lunchbox
Storyline: A mistaken delivery in Mumbai's famously efficient lunchbox delivery system connects a young housewife to an older man in the dusk of his life as they build a fantasy world together through notes in the lunchbox.

Name: Amy
Storyline: Archival footage and personal testimonials present an intimate portrait of the life and career of British singer/songwriter Amy Winehouse.

Name: Oliver Twist
Storyline: In Charles Dickens' classic tale, an orphan wends his way from cruel apprenticeship to den of thieves in search of a true home.

Name: Playtime
Storyline: Monsieur Hulot curiously wanders around a high-tech Paris, paralleling a trip with a group of American tourists. Meanwhile, a nightclub/restaurant prepares its opening night, but it's still under construction.

Name: A Night at the Opera
Storyline: A sly business manager and the wacky friends of two opera singers in Italy help them achieve success in America while humiliating their stuffy and snobbish enemies.

Name: Days of Wine and Roses
Storyline: An alcoholic marries a young woman and systematically addicts her to booze so that they can share his "passion" together.

Name: The Killer
Storyline: A disillusioned assassin accepts one last hit in hopes of using his earnings to restore vision to a singer he accidentally blinded.

Name: The Muppet Christmas Carol
Storyline: The Muppets present their own touching rendition of Charles Dickens' classic tale.

Name: The Asphalt Jungle
Storyline: A major heist goes off as planned, but then double crosses, bad luck and solid police work cause everything to unravel.

Name: They Shoot Horses, Don't They?
Storyline: The lives of a disparate group of contestants intertwine in an inhumanely grueling dance marathon.

Name: Tokyo Godfathers
Storyline: On Christmas Eve, three homeless people living on the streets of Tokyo discover a newborn baby among the trash and set out to find its parents.

Name: Millennium Actress
Storyline: A TV interviewer and his cameraman meet a former actress and travel through her memories and career.

Name: Crimes and Misdemeanors
Storyline: An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated with another woman.

Name: The Train
Storyline: In 1944, a German colonel loads a train with French art treasures to send to Germany. The Resistance must stop it without damaging the cargo.

Name: Seven Days in May
Storyline: United States military leaders plot to overthrow the President because he supports a nuclear disarmament treaty and they fear a Soviet sneak attack.

Name: The Ghost and Mrs. Muir
Storyline: In 1900, a young widow finds her seaside cottage is haunted and forms a unique relationship with the ghost.

Name: Breaker Morant
Storyline: Three Australian lieutenants are court martialed for executing prisoners as a way of deflecting attention from war crimes committed by their superior officers.

Name: Cléo from 5 to 7
Storyline: Cleo, a singer and hypochondriac, becomes increasingly worried that she might have cancer while awaiting test results from her doctor.

Name: Brother
Storyline: An ex-soldier with a personal honor code enters the family crime business in St. Petersburg, Russia.

Name: That Obscure Object of Desire
Storyline: Recounted in flashback are the romantic perils of Mathieu, a middle-aged French sophisticate as he falls for his nineteen-year-old former chambermaid Conchita.

Name: The Hunchback of Notre Dame
Storyline: In 15th-century France, a gypsy girl is framed for murder by the infatuated Chief Justice, and only the deformed bellringer of Notre Dame Cathedral can save her.

Name: My Life to Live
Storyline: Twelve episodic tales in the life of a Parisian woman and her slow descent into prostitution.

Name: The Children's Hour
Storyline: A rebellious student at a girls' school accuses two teachers of lesbianism.

Name: Becket
Storyline: King Henry II of England comes to terms with his affection for his close friend and confidant Thomas Becket, who finds his true honor by observing God's divine will rather than the King's.

Name: Balthazar
Storyline: The story of a mistreated donkey and the people around him. A study on saintliness and a sister piece to Bresson's Mouchette.

Name: Hiroshima Mon Amour
Storyline: A French actress filming an anti-war film in Hiroshima has an affair with a married Japanese architect as they share their differing perspectives on war.

Name: Ernest & Celestine
Storyline: The story of an unlikely friendship between a bear, Ernest, and a young mouse named Celestine.

Name: American Movie
Storyline: Documentary about an aspiring filmmaker's attempts to finance his dream project by finally completing the low-budget horror film he abandoned years before.

Name: Embrace of the Serpent
Storyline: The story of the relationship between Karamakate, an Amazonian shaman and last survivor of his people, and two scientists who work together over the course of forty years to search the Amazon for a sacred healing plant.

Name: The Spirit of the Beehive
Storyline: In 1940, after watching and being traumatized by the movie Frankenstein (1931), a sensitive seven year-old girl living in a small Spanish village drifts into her own fantasy world.

Name: Eat Drink Man Woman
Storyline: A senior chef lives with his three grown daughters; the middle one finds her future plans affected by unexpected events and the life changes of the other household members.

Name: Berserk: The Golden Age Arc III - The Advent
Storyline: A year has passed since Guts parted ways with Griffith. The Band of the Hawk is plotting a rescue mission to save Griffith who is confined to prison.

Name: Marvellous
Storyline: The life of Neil Baldwin, a man who has shrugged off his perceived limitations to live an incredible life.

Name: The Servant
Storyline: Upper-class Tony hires servant Hugo Barrett, who turns out to have a hidden agenda.

Name: An Elephant Sitting Still
Storyline: Four people in a Chinese city live through a complicated day as their lives intersect.

Name: The Set-Up
Storyline: Expecting the usual loss, a boxing manager takes bribes from a betting gangster without telling his fighter.

Name: Who Killed Captain Alex?
Storyline: Uganda's president gives Captain Alex an assignment to defeat the Tiger Mafia, but he gets killed in the process. Upon hearing the tragic news, his brother investigates to avenge Alex's death.

Name: My Night at Maud's
Storyline: A devout Catholic man's rigid principles are challenged during a one-night stay with Maud, a divorced woman with an outsize personality.

Name: My Life as a Zucchini
Storyline: After losing his mother, a young boy is sent to an orphanage with other orphans his age where he begins to learn the meaning of trust and true love.

Name: Destiny
Storyline: Bekir loves Ugur, who loves Zagor, who is about to get out of jail. An already tense love triangle is thrown into turmoil on a hot summer night, when Zagor kills someone, and Ugur disappears.

Name: Jiro Dreams of Sushi
Storyline: A documentary on 85-year-old sushi master Jiro Ono, his renowned Tokyo restaurant, and his relationship with his son and eventual heir, Yoshikazu.

Name: Ninotchka
Storyline: A stern Soviet woman sent to Paris to supervise the sale of jewels seized from Russian nobles finds herself attracted to a man who represents everything she is supposed to detest.

Name: Pelle the Conqueror
Storyline: When his wife dies, Lasse takes his 12-year-old son, Pelle, from their home in Sweden to Denmark in search of a better life.

Name: Birdman of Alcatraz
Storyline: A surly convicted murderer held in permanent isolation redeems himself when he becomes a renowned bird expert.

Name: The Mother and the Whore
Storyline: The chauvinist Alexandre balances relationships with several women, including the maternal Marie and the sexually liberated Veronika, in the post-1968 intellectual scene of Paris.

Name: Sword of the Stranger
Storyline: A swordsman from a strange land is caught in a struggle between morality, righteousness, and devotion as he reluctantly agrees to take a raggedy boy and his dog to a remote, Buddhist temple.

Name: System Crasher
Storyline: 9-year-old Benni is a toss-up between institutions that cannot tackle her outbursts. She wants to move in with her mother, but she can not handle her wild daughter. After Micha is hired Benni slowly opens up and attaches herself to him.

Name: Mr. Deeds Goes to Town
Storyline: A unassuming greeting card poet from a small town in Vermont heads to New York City upon inheriting a massive fortune and is immediately hounded by those who wish to take advantage of him.

Name: The Silence
Storyline: Two estranged sisters, Ester and Anna, and Anna's 10-year-old son travel to the Central European country on the verge of war. Ester becomes seriously ill and the three of them move into a hotel in a small town called Timoka.

Name: Poetry
Storyline: A sixty-something woman, faced with the discovery of a heinous family crime and in the early stages of Alzheimer's disease, finds strength and purpose when she enrolls in a poetry class.

Name: Pandora's Box
Storyline: The rise and inevitable fall of an amoral but naive young woman whose insouciant eroticism inspires lust and violence in those around her.

Name: Stray Dog
Storyline: During a sweltering summer, a rookie homicide detective tries to track down his stolen Colt pistol.

Name: C.R.A.Z.Y.
Storyline: A young French Canadian, one of five boys in a conservative family in the 1960s and 1970s, struggles to reconcile his emerging identity with his father's values.

Name: I Vitelloni
Storyline: A character study of five young men at crucial turning points in their lives in a small town in Italy.

Name: My Best Fiend
Storyline: The love-hate relationship between Werner Herzog and Klaus Kinski, the deep trust between the director and the actor, and their independently and simultaneously hatched plans to murder one another.

Name: The Bad and the Beautiful
Storyline: An unscrupulous movie producer uses an actress, a director and a writer to achieve success.

Name: A City of Sadness
Storyline: The story of a family embroiled in the "White Terror" that was wrought on the Taiwanese people by the Kuomintang government after their arrival from mainland China in the late 1940s.

Name: Of Mice and Men
Storyline: A mentally disabled giant and his level headed guardian find work at a sadistic cowboy's ranch in depression era America.

Name: In This Corner (and Other Corners) of the World
Storyline: A spirited 18-year-old woman is married off to a man she barely knows as she combats the daily struggles of living in Hiroshima during World War II.

Name: The Phantom of Liberty
Storyline: A series of surreal sequences that critique morality and society in a stream of consciousness style.

Name: The Fire Within
Storyline: Depressed Alain Leroy leaves the clinic where he was detoxified. He meets friends, acquaintances and women, trying to find a reason to continue living. Will this help him?

Name: Good Morning
Storyline: Two boys begin a silence strike to press their parents into buying them a television set.

Name: El Sur
Storyline: A woman reflects on her childhood relationship with her father, attempting to understand the depths of his despair and the truth of his myths.

Name: Muscle Shoals
Storyline: A documentary that celebrates Rick Hall, the founder of FAME Studios in Muscle Shoals, Alabama, and the signature sound he developed in songs such as "I'll Take You There", "Brown Sugar", and "When a Man Loves a Woman".

Name: The Sparks Brothers
Storyline: A musical odyssey through five weird and wonderful decades with Ron and Russell Mael celebrating the inspiring legacy of Sparks.

Name: White Nights
Storyline: A humble clerk courts a woman who awaits her lover's return night after night.

Name: The Ballad of Narayama
Storyline: In a poor 19th century rural Japanese village, everyone who reaches the age of 70 has to climb a nearby mountain to die. An elderly woman is reaching close to her cut-off age during her last days with her family.

Name: A Tale of Two Cities

Name: Victoria

A feature film which presents deleted scenes from Twin Peaks: Fire Walk with Me (1992) assembled together for the first time in an untold portion of the story's prequel.

Name: The 36th Chamber of Shaolin

Name: A Summer's Tale
Storyline: A shy maths graduate takes a holiday in Dinard before starting his first job. He hopes his sort-of girlfriend will join him, but soon strikes up a friendship with another girl working in ...                See full summary »

Storyline: Prince Hamlet struggles over whether or not he should kill his uncle, whom he suspects has murdered his father, the former king.

Name: Public Speaking
